caption: Great atmosphere. Tasty food. Helpful staff. Owner/Manager was prompt and helpful. Cris was helpful and greeted me at the door.
The tacos were great and that free margarita for the Taco Tuesday special was amazing 🥴... wish there was lengua on the menu.

Have you ever been dead and came back to life. Rebel Taco is the best taco joint you can find in DC. They’re specialty tacos are freckin’ amazing and their churros are lose your mind. Pair them with the Rebel Margarita and you’re guaranteed to have an incredible date night, or awesome dinner out! We’re coming back for brunch :)

Dios mio!  This place is awesome.  Had the brunch and it was on point.  I grew up in a Mexican restaurant environment in East LA.  Huevos rancheros, steak and eggs and drinks. Desert, my soft spot melted my heart.  Warm churros, fondue Mexican chamurrado flavored warm chocolate....Decor and vibe is fun and chingon.
Drinks: A1 Food: A1 Management: A1  Mark my words, this will definitely be one of the dopest places near U st when everything goes back to normal

Where do I start...! First time at rebel taco. The vibe was awesome. Super clean and chill. The food...? The food was amazing instagram definitely sold me on the birria taco was amazing, chips and guacamole was very good as well. The Mexican tacos was super yummy. Mauricio was the nicest. He was super energized and ready to help and answered all of our questions. Super nice guy. I’d recommend this place to everyone and will definitely be back.
Tacos are good. Prices are insane.
This is the most overpriced taco place I have ever seen for the smallest taco I have ever eating. It was good but not great for the price!

Sadly disappointed with our meal here. We ordered 3 tacos (chicken, short rib, and brisket). While the taste was okay (the brisket was good, though) there was barely meat on the tacos. Especially on the chicken taco, it was basically all pico de Gallo and the tiniest portion of chicken. We also ordered the steak burrito. It was terrible. There wasn’t much meat and it tasted worse than Taco Bell. The guacamole was good, but the the chips weren’t even great. I hate to give a bad rating to a new restaurant, especially during covid, but the food just wasn’t great. Pro: fast takeout and cleanliness helped the rating.
This place is fantastic! Tacos with fresh ingredients, full of flavor, and served on handmade tortillas. Service was friendly and prompt. The queso with jalepenos is so hot! Yum!

5 STAR TACOS!!!! So happy to have come here and can't wait to come back! Every single taco we tried was delicious, and generously filled. Our faves were the brisket, smoke show, tuna, shrimp, BARRIA DE REZ...actually, I can keep going because we almost tried them all and they were ALL GREAT!!! And the food all came to our table so fast! Watermelon margaritas were awesome, queso Blanco was so tasty, waitress was very nice. Not a bad thing to say about this place. Will definitely recommend to my friends!
Delicious takeout and friendly staff. The ‘shrimp gone wild’ taco is bomb!
Best tacos I’ve had in DC. Outdoor patio has a great ambiance and the service is excellent. I highly recommend this new spot.
